wikipedia_page.main: Horace Stanley Keats (20 July 1895 – 21 August 1945) was an English-born Australian composer, arranger, piano accompanist and conductor.  As a composer he was most noted for his 115 songs, which caused an Australian academic to dub him "the Schubert of Australia" and others to call him "the poets' composer". He also wrote ballet music, film scores, choral works, incidental music and a musical.
